results.name: T(n,k) is the number of labeled graphs of n vertices and k edges that have endpoints, where an endpoint is a vertex with degree 1.
comment: Let j = (n-1)*(n-2)/2.  For i >=0, n >= 4+i, T(n,j-i+1) = n*(n-1)*binomial(j,i).
For k <= 3, T(n,k) is equal to the number of labeled bipartite graphs with n vertices and k edges.  In particular, T(n,1) = A000217(n-1), T(n,2) = A050534(n) and T(n,3) = A053526(n).
link: C. W. Wu, Graphs whose normalized Laplacian matrices are separable as density matrices in quantum mechanics, arXiv:1407.5663 [quant-ph], 2014.
xref: Sum of n-th row is A245797(n).
